Note:
CONFIG_VALUE - Generic configuration value tree (Tier 1)

Builds on top of config.runa to add operations beyond the base CV_* API:
  - DateTime (CV_DATETIME) and Duration (CV_DURATION) variants for
    typed config (covers TOML 1.0 date/time and duration scalars).
  - Path-aware get/set helpers across CV_MAP-CV_LIST hierarchies.
  - Deep merge with override semantics (used by configuration layer
    overlays).
  - Native Runa-format round-trip (config_value_to_runa_native /
    config_value_from_runa_native).

The kind tag layout reuses CV_* constants where available (0..6) and
introduces CV_DATETIME=7 and CV_DURATION=8 here. DateTime values are
stored as ISO-8601 UTC strings; Duration values are stored as Integer
nanoseconds. These representations are loss-free for the relevant
TOML/YAML scalars and avoid pulling in the time module at this tier.

References:
  - TOML 1.0 ........ https://toml.io/en/v1.0.0
  - YAML 1.2 ........ https://yaml.org/spec/1.2.2/
  - INI (de facto) .. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/INI_file
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/config/config.runa" as Cfg

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS - extended kinds
Note: ============================================================================

Note: CV_NULL ... CV_MAP live in config.runa (0..6).
Let CV_DATETIME be 7
Let CV_DURATION be 8

Note: Reuse the same 24-byte ConfigValue layout. The extended kinds use
Note: the existing data and len_or_flags slots. CV_SIZE is defined in
Note: config.runa and flattened into this module via the import of Cfg.

Note: ============================================================================
Note: EXTENDED CONSTRUCTORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Construct a CV_DATETIME wrapping an ISO-8601 string. The string is
duplicated so the value owns it. Validation of the input format is the
caller's responsibility (or the TOML/YAML parser's).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate string, allocate 24-byte record, store kind/pointer/length.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "config_value_datetime" takes iso_text as Integer returns Integer:
    If iso_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with iso_text
    If copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let v be proc allocate from Layout with CV_SIZE
    If v is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 0, CV_DATETIME
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 8, copy
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 16, length
    Return v
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a CV_DURATION storing nanoseconds inline.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 24-byte record; store kind and ns value inline.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Accepts any 64-bit signed integer ns.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "config_value_duration" takes nanoseconds as Integer returns Integer:
    Let v be proc allocate from Layout with CV_SIZE
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 0, CV_DURATION
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 8, nanoseconds
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with v, 16, 0
    Return v
End Process

@Reasoning
Extract the ISO-8601 string from a CV_DATETIME value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Verify kind, load data pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on type mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "config_value_as_datetime" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 0
    If kind is not equal to CV_DATETIME:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Extract the nanoseconds from a CV_DURATION.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Verify kind, load inline data.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on type mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "config_value_as_duration" takes v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 0
    If kind is not equal to CV_DURATION:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PATH-AWARE GET / SET
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Resolve a dotted path against a ConfigValue tree where intermediate
nodes may be CV_MAP or CV_LIST (the latter using zero-based numeric
indexes as path segments). Returns the value at the path, or 0 if any
segment is missing or has a wrong kind.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk the path segment by segment. At each step:
  - Find the next dot delimiter; substring the segment.
  - If current value is CV_MAP, dictionary lookup by segment.
  - Else if CV_LIST and segment is all-digits, list_get by integer
    index.
  - Else fail.
At end of path, return the current value.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|path|). Space: O(|segment|) for the per-step substring (freed
each iteration).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on any missing segment, type mismatch, or empty path.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "config_value_get" takes root as Integer, dotted_path as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If dotted_path is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with dotted_path
    If length is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let current be root
    Let seg_start be 0
    Let i be 0
    Let going be 1
    While going is equal to 1:
        Let at_dot be 0
        Let at_end be 0
        If i is greater than or equal to length:
            Set at_end to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with dotted_path, i
            If ch is equal to 46:
                Set at_dot to 1
            End If
        End If
        If at_end is equal to 1:
            Let seg_len be i minus seg_start
            If seg_len is less than 1:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let seg be proc string_substring from StringPrim with dotted_path, seg_start, seg_len
            If seg is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Set current to proc lookup_segment with current, seg
            proc deallocate from Layout with seg
            Set going to 0
        Otherwise:
            If at_dot is equal to 1:
                Let seg_len2 be i minus seg_start
                If seg_len2 is less than 1:
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let seg2 be proc string_substring from StringPrim with dotted_path, seg_start, seg_len2
                If seg2 is equal to 0:
                    Return 0
                End If
                Set current to proc lookup_segment with current, seg2
                proc deallocate from Layout with seg2
                If current is equal to 0:
                    Return 0
                End If
                Set seg_start to i plus 1
                Set i to i plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return current
End Process

@Reasoning
Look up a single segment against a value. Dispatches based on kind: map
key for CV_MAP, integer index for CV_LIST.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Inspect kind. CV_MAP: dict_get. CV_LIST: parse seg as integer, list_get.
Otherwise return 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) for map, O(1) for list.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "lookup_segment" takes value as Integer, segment as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, 0
    If kind is equal to 6:
        Let map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, 8
        Return proc get from Dict with map, segment
    End If
    If kind is equal to 5:
        Let arr be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, 8
        Let idx be proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with segment
        If idx is less than 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let len_arr be proc list_length from List with arr
        If idx is greater than or equal to len_arr:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc list_get from List with arr, idx
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Set a value at a dotted path. Intermediate CV_MAP nodes are created on
demand; intermediate CV_LIST nodes must already exist with sufficient
length. Returns 1 on success, 0 if the path cannot be created (e.g. an
intermediate is a non-map scalar that would have to be replaced).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Split the path. At each step except the last, ensure the current value
is a CV_MAP; if not present, create a new one and attach. Step into it.
At the last step, replace any existing value.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|path|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if intermediate kinds collide.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "config_value_set" takes root as Integer, dotted_path as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If dotted_path is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with root, 0
    If root_kind is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let current_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with root, 8
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with dotted_path
    Let i be 0
    Let seg_start be 0
    Let going be 1
    While going is equal to 1:
        Let at_end be 0
        If i is greater than or equal to length:
            Set at_end to 1
        End If
        Let is_dot be 0
        If at_end is equal to 0:
            Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with dotted_path, i
            If ch is equal to 46:
                Set is_dot to 1
            End If
        End If
        If at_end is equal to 1:
            Let seg_len be i minus seg_start
            If seg_len is less than 1:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let seg be proc string_substring from StringPrim with dotted_path, seg_start, seg_len
            If seg is equal to 0:
                Return 0
            End If
            Let prior be proc get from Dict with current_map, seg
            If prior is not equal to 0:
                proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with prior
            End If
            proc set from Dict with current_map, seg, value
            proc deallocate from Layout with seg
            Set going to 0
        Otherwise:
            If is_dot is equal to 1:
                Let seg_len2 be i minus seg_start
                If seg_len2 is less than 1:
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let seg2 be proc string_substring from StringPrim with dotted_path, seg_start, seg_len2
                If seg2 is equal to 0:
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let existing be proc get from Dict with current_map, seg2
                If existing is equal to 0:
                    Let new_dict be proc create from Dict
                    If new_dict is equal to 0:
                        proc deallocate from Layout with seg2
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    Let new_map_value be proc config_value_map from Cfg with new_dict
                    If new_map_value is equal to 0:
                        proc destroy from Dict with new_dict
                        proc deallocate from Layout with seg2
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    proc set from Dict with current_map, seg2, new_map_value
                    Set current_map to new_dict
                Otherwise:
                    Let existing_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with existing, 0
                    If existing_kind is not equal to 6:
                        proc deallocate from Layout with seg2
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    Set current_map to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with existing, 8
                End If
                proc deallocate from Layout with seg2
                Set seg_start to i plus 1
                Set i to i plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DEEP MERGE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Deep-merge two ConfigValue trees. The result becomes the union of the
base and overlay, where overlay wins for any colliding key. CV_MAP
values recursively merge; CV_LIST and scalar values from overlay replace
the base value. The base tree is mutated in place and now owns any
adopted overlay subtrees; the overlay scaffolding (dictionary headers,
list headers, value-records that were merged into) is freed.

This is the semantics used by 12-factor config overlays and by Cargo /
npm dependency resolution.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
If base or overlay is null, do nothing or transfer ownership. If either
is non-map, replace base with overlay (caller owns the result). For map
+ map, iterate overlay keys; for each, if base has it and both are
maps, recurse. Otherwise destroy the base value and adopt overlay's
value pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over overlay subtree.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 1 on success; 0 if base is null or kinds incompatible.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "config_value_merge" takes base as Integer, overlay as Integer returns Integer:
    If base is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If overlay is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let bk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with base, 0
    Let ok2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with overlay, 0
    If bk is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    If ok2 is not equal to 6:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bd be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with base, 8
    Let od be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with overlay, 8
    Let okeys be proc keys from Dict with od
    If okeys is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let oc be proc list_length from List with okeys
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than oc:
        Let okey be proc list_get from List with okeys, i
        Let oval be proc get from Dict with od, okey
        Let bval be proc get from Dict with bd, okey
        If bval is equal to 0:
            proc set from Dict with bd, okey, oval
            proc set from Dict with od, okey, 0
        Otherwise:
            Let bvk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with bval, 0
            Let ovk be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with oval, 0
            If bvk is equal to 6:
                If ovk is equal to 6:
                    proc config_value_merge with bval, oval
                Otherwise:
                    proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with bval
                    proc set from Dict with bd, okey, oval
                    proc set from Dict with od, okey, 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                proc config_value_destroy from Cfg with bval
                proc set from Dict with bd, okey, oval
                proc set from Dict with od, okey, 0
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc list_destroy from List with okeys
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: RUNA-NATIVE FORMAT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Serialize a ConfigValue tree into the Runa-native config-value textual
format. The format is human-readable and round-trips via
config_value_from_runa_native.

Grammar:
  value     := scalar | "[" list "]" | "{" map "}"
  scalar    := "null" | "true" | "false" | integer | string-literal
             | "@datetime " ISO-string | "@duration " integer-ns
  list      := value ("," value)*
  map       := key " : " value ("," key " : " value)*
  key       := identifier | string-literal
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Recursive emitter using a StringBuilder. Map iteration order follows the
underlying dictionary keys.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "config_value_to_runa_native" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc emit_value with sb, value
    Let out be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return out
End Process

@Reasoning
Recursive emitter for one value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Switch on kind. CV_NULL/CV_BOOL/CV_INTEGER emit scalar tokens. CV_STRING
emits quoted form. CV_LIST emits "[a,b,c]". CV_MAP emits "{k:v,k:v}".
CV_DATETIME emits "@datetime <iso>". CV_DURATION emits "@duration <ns>".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "emit_value" takes sb as Integer, v as Integer returns Integer:
    If v is equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "null"
        Return 1
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 0
    If kind is equal to 0:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "null"
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 4:
        Let b be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
        If b is equal to 1:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "true"
        Otherwise:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "false"
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 2:
        Let iv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
        proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, iv
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 1:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
        Let sp be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
        If sp is not equal to 0:
            Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with sp
            Let i be 0
            While i is less than length:
                Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with sp, i
                If ch is equal to 34:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
                Otherwise:
                    If ch is equal to 92:
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                    Otherwise:
                        If ch is equal to 10:
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 92
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 110
                        Otherwise:
                            proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 5:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 91
        Let arr be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
        If arr is not equal to 0:
            Let lc be proc list_length from List with arr
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than lc:
                Let elem be proc list_get from List with arr, j
                If j is greater than 0:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 44
                End If
                proc emit_value with sb, elem
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 93
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to 6:
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 123
        Let map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
        If map is not equal to 0:
            Let mk be proc keys from Dict with map
            If mk is not equal to 0:
                Let mc be proc list_length from List with mk
                Let k be 0
                While k is less than mc:
                    Let key be proc list_get from List with mk, k
                    Let val be proc get from Dict with map, key
                    If k is greater than 0:
                        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 44
                    End If
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
                    If key is not equal to 0:
                        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, key
                    End If
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 34
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 58
                    proc emit_value with sb, val
                    Set k to k plus 1
                End While
                proc list_destroy from List with mk
            End If
        End If
        proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 125
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to CV_DATETIME:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "@datetime "
        Let dt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
        If dt is not equal to 0:
            proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, dt
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If kind is equal to CV_DURATION:
        proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "@duration "
        Let ns be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with v, 8
        proc stringbuilder_append_integer from SB with sb, ns
        Return 1
    End If
    proc stringbuilder_append from SB with sb, "null"
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a Runa-native config-value textual representation into a
ConfigValue tree. The format produced by config_value_to_runa_native is
the canonical input.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Recursive descent over the input bytes. The parser tracks position in a
small state record and dispatches on the next non-whitespace byte:
  'n'  -> "null"
  't'  -> "true"
  'f'  -> "false"
  '"'  -> string literal
  '['  -> list
  '{'  -> map
  '@'  -> typed marker (@datetime / @duration)
  digit / '-' -> integer
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "config_value_from_runa_native" takes text as Integer returns Integer:
    If text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let state be proc allocate from Layout with 24
    If state is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 0, text
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 8, length
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, 0
    Let value be proc rv_parse_value with state
    proc deallocate from Layout with state
    Return value
End Process

@Reasoning
Skip ASCII whitespace at the current cursor position.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Advance while byte is space/tab/LF/CR.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(k).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Internal.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rv_skip_ws" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    While pos is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
        Let is_ws be 0
        If ch is equal to 32:
            Set is_ws to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 9:
            Set is_ws to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 10:
            Set is_ws to 1
        End If
        If ch is equal to 13:
            Set is_ws to 1
        End If
        If is_ws is equal to 0:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos
            Return 1
        End If
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse one value at the cursor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Dispatch on first byte.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rv_parse_value" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    proc rv_skip_ws with state
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If pos is greater than or equal to length:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
    If ch is equal to 110:
        Return proc rv_parse_literal_value with state, "null", 0
    End If
    If ch is equal to 116:
        Return proc rv_parse_literal_value with state, "true", 1
    End If
    If ch is equal to 102:
        Return proc rv_parse_literal_value with state, "false", 2
    End If
    If ch is equal to 34:
        Let s be proc rv_parse_string with state
        If s is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let cv be proc config_value_string from Cfg with s
        proc deallocate from Layout with s
        Return cv
    End If
    If ch is equal to 91:
        Return proc rv_parse_list with state
    End If
    If ch is equal to 123:
        Return proc rv_parse_map with state
    End If
    If ch is equal to 64:
        Return proc rv_parse_typed_marker with state
    End If
    Let isdig be 0
    If ch is greater than or equal to 48:
        If ch is less than or equal to 57:
            Set isdig to 1
        End If
    End If
    If ch is equal to 45:
        Set isdig to 1
    End If
    If isdig is equal to 1:
        Return proc rv_parse_integer with state
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Match a literal keyword and produce the corresponding ConfigValue.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Verify next |literal| bytes match; on success advance and produce the
specified value:
  flag=0 -> null
  flag=1 -> true
  flag=2 -> false
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(|literal|).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on mismatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rv_parse_literal_value" takes state as Integer, literal as Integer, flag as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    Let llen be proc string_length from StringCore with literal
    If (pos plus llen) is greater than length:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than llen:
        Let a be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos plus i
        Let b be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with literal, i
        If a is not equal to b:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos plus llen
    If flag is equal to 0:
        Return proc config_value_null from Cfg
    End If
    If flag is equal to 1:
        Return proc config_value_bool from Cfg with 1
    End If
    Return proc config_value_bool from Cfg with 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a quoted string literal at the cursor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Consume opening '"'. Walk bytes decoding \\, \", \n. Stop at closing '"'.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on unterminated.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rv_parse_string" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If pos is greater than or equal to length:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let opener be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
    If opener is not equal to 34:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let sb be proc stringbuilder_create from SB
    If sb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let done be 0
    While done is equal to 0:
        If pos is greater than or equal to length:
            proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
            Return 0
        End If
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        If ch is equal to 34:
            Set done to 1
        Otherwise:
            If ch is equal to 92:
                If pos is greater than or equal to length:
                    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
                    Return 0
                End If
                Let esc be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
                Set pos to pos plus 1
                If esc is equal to 110:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, 10
                Otherwise:
                    proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, esc
                End If
            Otherwise:
                proc stringbuilder_append_char from SB with sb, ch
            End If
        End If
    End While
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos
    Let s be proc stringbuilder_to_string from SB with sb
    proc stringbuilder_destroy from SB with sb
    Return s
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a "[...]" list of values.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Consume '['. Skip ws. If ']', done. Else loop parsing values separated
by ','.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rv_parse_list" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If pos is greater than or equal to length:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let opener be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
    If opener is not equal to 91:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos
    Let lst be proc list_create from List
    If lst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc rv_skip_ws with state
    Let new_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If new_pos is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, new_pos
        If ch is equal to 93:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, new_pos plus 1
            Return proc config_value_list from Cfg with lst
        End If
    End If
    Let going be 1
    While going is equal to 1:
        proc rv_skip_ws with state
        Let elem be proc rv_parse_value with state
        If elem is equal to 0:
            proc list_destroy from List with lst
            Return 0
        End If
        proc list_push from List with lst, elem
        proc rv_skip_ws with state
        Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
        If cur is greater than or equal to length:
            proc list_destroy from List with lst
            Return 0
        End If
        Let nch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, cur
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, cur plus 1
        If nch is equal to 93:
            Set going to 0
        Otherwise:
            If nch is not equal to 44:
                proc list_destroy from List with lst
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return proc config_value_list from Cfg with lst
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a "{key:value,...}" map.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Consume '{', loop parsing string-quoted keys and values separated by
':' and ','.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rv_parse_map" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If pos is greater than or equal to length:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let opener be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
    If opener is not equal to 123:
        Return 0
    End If
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos
    Let map be proc create from Dict
    If map is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc rv_skip_ws with state
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    If cur is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, cur
        If ch is equal to 125:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, cur plus 1
            Return proc config_value_map from Cfg with map
        End If
    End If
    Let going be 1
    While going is equal to 1:
        proc rv_skip_ws with state
        Let key be proc rv_parse_string with state
        If key is equal to 0:
            proc destroy from Dict with map
            Return 0
        End If
        proc rv_skip_ws with state
        Let cpos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
        If cpos is greater than or equal to length:
            proc deallocate from Layout with key
            proc destroy from Dict with map
            Return 0
        End If
        Let colon be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, cpos
        If colon is not equal to 58:
            proc deallocate from Layout with key
            proc destroy from Dict with map
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, cpos plus 1
        Let val be proc rv_parse_value with state
        If val is equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with key
            proc destroy from Dict with map
            Return 0
        End If
        proc set from Dict with map, key, val
        proc deallocate from Layout with key
        proc rv_skip_ws with state
        Let after be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
        If after is greater than or equal to length:
            proc destroy from Dict with map
            Return 0
        End If
        Let nch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, after
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, after plus 1
        If nch is equal to 125:
            Set going to 0
        Otherwise:
            If nch is not equal to 44:
                proc destroy from Dict with map
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Return proc config_value_map from Cfg with map
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse "@datetime <iso>" or "@duration <ns>" typed-marker values.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Consume '@'. Read identifier. Skip whitespace. For datetime parse a
non-whitespace token. For duration parse an integer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on unknown marker.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rv_parse_typed_marker" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let marker_start be pos
    While pos is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
        Let is_ws be 0
        If ch is equal to 32:
            Set is_ws to 1
        End If
        If is_ws is equal to 1:
            Set pos to length plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
    End While
    Let marker_end be marker_start
    Let scan be 1
    While scan is equal to 1:
        If marker_end is greater than or equal to length:
            Set scan to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let ch2 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, marker_end
            If ch2 is equal to 32:
                Set scan to 0
            Otherwise:
                Set marker_end to marker_end plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Let mlen be marker_end minus marker_start
    Let marker be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, marker_start, mlen
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, marker_end
    proc rv_skip_ws with state
    Let is_dt be proc string_equals from StringCore with marker, "datetime"
    Let is_dur be proc string_equals from StringCore with marker, "duration"
    proc deallocate from Layout with marker
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    Let arg_start be cur
    Let scan2 be 1
    While scan2 is equal to 1:
        If cur is greater than or equal to length:
            Set scan2 to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let ch3 be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, cur
            Let is_ws3 be 0
            If ch3 is equal to 32:
                Set is_ws3 to 1
            End If
            If ch3 is equal to 9:
                Set is_ws3 to 1
            End If
            If ch3 is equal to 10:
                Set is_ws3 to 1
            End If
            If ch3 is equal to 13:
                Set is_ws3 to 1
            End If
            If ch3 is equal to 44:
                Set is_ws3 to 1
            End If
            If ch3 is equal to 125:
                Set is_ws3 to 1
            End If
            If ch3 is equal to 93:
                Set is_ws3 to 1
            End If
            If is_ws3 is equal to 1:
                Set scan2 to 0
            Otherwise:
                Set cur to cur plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Let alen be cur minus arg_start
    Let arg be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, arg_start, alen
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, cur
    If is_dt is equal to 1:
        Let v be proc config_value_datetime with arg
        proc deallocate from Layout with arg
        Return v
    End If
    If is_dur is equal to 1:
        Let ns be proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with arg
        proc deallocate from Layout with arg
        Return proc config_value_duration with ns
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with arg
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a signed decimal integer at the cursor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Optionally consume '-'. Read digits until non-digit. Substring, convert,
wrap as CV_INTEGER.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(d) digits.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rv_parse_integer" takes state as Integer returns Integer:
    Let text be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 0
    Let length be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 8
    Let pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with state, 16
    Let start be pos
    If pos is less than length:
        Let ch be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
        If ch is equal to 45:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
    End If
    Let any_digit be 0
    Let going be 1
    While going is equal to 1:
        If pos is greater than or equal to length:
            Set going to 0
        Otherwise:
            Let cd be proc memory_get_byte from Memory with text, pos
            Let isd be 0
            If cd is greater than or equal to 48:
                If cd is less than or equal to 57:
                    Set isd to 1
                End If
            End If
            If isd is equal to 1:
                Set pos to pos plus 1
                Set any_digit to 1
            Otherwise:
                Set going to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    If any_digit is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let slen be pos minus start
    Let span be proc string_substring from StringPrim with text, start, slen
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with state, 16, pos
    Let iv be proc string_to_integer from StringPrim with span
    proc deallocate from Layout with span
    Return proc config_value_integer from Cfg with iv
End Process
